OL,7,FAfter the verdict, mothers Allison and
OL,8,FRuth Cooper-Hall shared a statement
OL,9,Fsaying the "hopes and dreams we had on
OL,10,Fthe birth of our son Giles have been
OL,11,Fcompletely shattered".
OL,13,FRuth Cooper-Hall was 41 weeks into her
OL,14,Fpregnancy when she experienced reduced
OL,15,Ffoetal movement.
OL,17,FSenior doctor, Dr Alexander Taylor,
OL,18,Fdrew up a care plan which stressed the
OL,19,Fimportance of closely monitoring her
OL,20,Fbaby's heart rate.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G2/10
